preview: # Must Have
title: Optimize-Web
tags: Web Optimization
author: rrLero
date: 18-02-14 22:31
---
**Must Have**

1. Use CDN
1. JS - bottom, CSS - top
1. Add expires or cache control to Headers
1. GZIP components
1. avoid CSS expressions
1. external JS and CSS
1. reduce DNS lookup
1. minify JS/CSS
1. avoid filters
1. post/pre load components
1. reduce number of DOM els
1. split components across  domains
1. minimize the # of iframes
1. 404s
1. reduce cookie size
1. cookie free domains for components
1. minimize DOM access
1. keep components under 25K
1. avoid empty image src
1. reduce redirects
1. remove duplicate scripts
1. configure ETags
1. cache AJAX
1. optimize images
1. optimize sprites
1. don't scale images
1. small and cacheable favicons
1. choose <link> over @import

https://developer.yahoo.com/performance/rules.html 

**CHECKLIST**

* Avoid landing page redirects
* Enable compression
* Improve server response time
* Leverage browser caching
* Minify resources
* Optimize images
* Optimize CSS Delivery
* Prioritize visible content
* Remove render-blocking JavaScript
* Use asynchronous scripts

https://developers.google.com/speed/docs/insights/rules

